             English Premier League soccer club
Manchester City said it signed Barcelona midfielder  Yaya Toure 
on a five-year contract.  
 The Ivory Coast international had a medical exam today
before completing the details of his switch from the Spanish
champion, City said on its  website .  
 Toure, 28, will take a three-week vacation before joining
his new teammates, including elder brother Kolo, on Cityâ€™s
preseason tour of the U.S., the club said.  
          
          


  


        